  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "IoT Engineer",
  "description": "<p>We are seeking a skilled IoT Engineer to design, develop, and maintain Internet of Things (IoT) solutions that connect devices, sensors, and systems to deliver real-time data and actionable insights. The ideal candidate has a strong background in embedded systems, networking, cloud platforms, data integration and related programming skills, with a passion for building scalable, secure IoT architectures.</p><p></p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><p>Design, develop, and deploy end-to-end IoT solutions (devices, gateways, cloud, and applications)</p><p>Develop and maintain firmware for embedded devices and sensors</p><p>Integrate IoT devices with cloud platforms and backend systems</p><p>Implement communication protocols (e.g., MQTT, CoAP, HTTP, BLE, LoRaWAN, Zigbee)</p><p>Ensure data security, device authentication, and secure communication</p><p>Monitor, troubleshoot, and optimize device performance and connectivity</p><p>Collaborate with cross-functional teams (hardware, software, data, and product)</p><p>Create technical documentation for system architecture, APIs, and deployment processes</p><p>Support testing, validation, and field deployment of IoT systems</p><p></p><p><strong>Required Qualifications</strong></p><p>Bachelor’s degree in Computer Engineering, Electronics Engineering, Mechatronics Engineering or related field</p><p>Experience in developing IoT or embedded systems</p><p>Proficiency in programming languages such as C/C++, Python, or Java</p><p>Knowledge of networking concepts and wireless technologies</p>",
